AN ACT relating to courts; providing that certain proceedings and
causes of action may be brought in a qualified judicial
district; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, the First Judicial District Court has jurisdiction conferred
2 by statute over certain proceedings, including, without limitation, final decisions
3 made by the Secretary of State, Department of Transportation or Commissioner of
4 Insurance. (NRS 294A.420, 485.290, 693A.665) Existing law also confers the First
5 Judicial District Court with jurisdiction over certain causes of action, including,
6 without limitation, certain criminal petitions and certain disputes related to
7 property. (NRS 34.738, 120A.525, 485.290) Section 2 of this bill provides that the
8 jurisdiction conferred by statute to the First Judicial District Court over a cause of
9 action or other proceeding is also conferred by statute to any qualified judicial
10 district. Section 3 of this bill provides that any district court in a judicial district is a
11 qualified judicial district if it has: (1) three or more district judges; (2) an electronic
12 filing, storage and reproduction process; and (3) electronic access to its documents
13 and hearings.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. The preliminary chapter of NRS is hereby amended
2 by adding thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this
3 act.
4 Sec. 2. Except as otherwise expressly provided in a particular
5 statute or required by the context, any reference to the “First
